      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "When everything feels like ruins, the pressure to immediately \"build\" can feel crushing and pointless. Instead of focusing on building a whole new life, perhaps try focusing on small moments of gentle acknowledgement for the self you are currently inhabiting. These tiny moments of quiet presence, even without grand meaning attached, can sometimes offer a small reprieve from the feeling of merely being a caretaker. Reaching out to a support line can also offer non-judgmental company in these moments of profound emptiness.",
      "source": "target",
